💡 Placement Tip

In placement aptitude tests, basic logarithm questions usually require converting a number into a power of the base. Focus on understanding the relationship aˣ = N ⇔ logₐ(N) = x, memorize common powers of 2, 3, 5, and 10, and remember the three key identities:

logₐ(1) = 0

logₐ(a) = 1

logₐ(aⁿ) = n


Mastering these basics makes it much easier to learn advanced logarithm concepts such as logarithm laws and the change of base formula later.
